properties.Name: Black Friday 2p. 5.8
properties.description: Fun Chimney belay at the beginning of splitter hand crack. p.2 Climb the beautiful splitter in the left wall of the chimney. Traverse left around the roof and crimp your way to the top. There is a crack but dirt and rhodos keep you out of it. FA. Heath Rowland, Eric Davenport

properties.Name: Grab it and Growl 5.9
properties.description: This route is located on a ledge 40ft up but should not be missed. It is one of the most splitter hand cracks in the Gorge. The real crux is getting to it. The fa party used a throw ball to get a line in the tree, then jugged up to the ledge. At this time, there is a line you can use to pull your rope up in the tree. It's zaney but worth it. As for the route...Start jamming at the bottom finish at the top. Multiple 2's recommended. F.A. Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Hard Right 5.9
properties.description: Climb the perfect hand crack for 30ft then climb the protected traverse for 40ft. Rap from tree.

properties.Name: Roy 2p. 5.10
properties.description: Must do. Long. Exposed. Good Rock. p1. Climb 40ft of moderate terrain to the base of the crack. Start in the steepening body size offwidth to gain the steep hand and finger crack. Layback to the roof and escape right on sketchy rock and bad feet(good gear though) Belay in the alcove. 90ft p2. Climb the steep chimney, after ten feet look down and notice there is only air between you and the ground. Launch into the very exposed fist crack that finishes on a ledge. Catch your breathe then work your way up the awkward, insecure dihedral to the top. 80ft. Walk skiers right and rap off a tree that will land you on a ledge. Rap from here to the ground.

properties.Name: Relationship Goals 5.9+
properties.description: Splitter hands to offwidth to dirt. This would be classic if someone cleaned out the crack at the top. Could be a cool winter route if it gets wet and doesnt get cleaned. Moss hookin' shit! F.A* Eric Davenport, Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Flake Route 5.7
properties.description: Super fun, slightly dirty flake. Jam and stem your way to the top. F.A. Unknown

properties.Name: Project
properties.description: Dihedral to traverse to thin tips splitter. Loose rock on traverse.

properties.Name: Hand Sandwich 5.10-
properties.description: Fantastic over-hanging hand crack. No frills, just thrills. FA: Geoff Ris, Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Dihedral of Horrors 2p. 5.9
properties.description: p1. Climb the dihedral to the large roof and build a hanging belay. p2. Crawl and whimper your way across the ledge to the tree. The route can be finished at the top by climbing through the large roof. FA: Heath Rowland Geoff Ris 2015

properties.Name: Donnie Loves Steph 5.9pg13
properties.description: Either climb Crimp Connect or scramble to the top via a notch on the north side of the rock. Rappel down the face, pull the rope and climb the face placing gear where you can. The crux is well protected. The face is wide and could hold more routes. FA: Heath Rowland Jon Jugenhiemer

properties.Name: Crimp Connect 5.9+ R
properties.description: For hard asses only. Climb the fat/wide flake to its top. Build a nest and take off up and left on iron edges. Gain the crack, place a piece, then realize the crack is steeper than you thought. Climb the sustained, steep, sharp crack to the top. More of a stunt than a climb. 70ft. FA: Geoff Ris Heath Rowland

properties.Name: In Stitches 5.10
properties.description: Fingers to hands to the top. FA:Heath Rowland Jon Jugenhiemer

properties.Name: Thunder Trundle 5.10
properties.description: Sandy and unfinished. The FA took the route to the ledge and then traversed left to a tree. The crack system continues trough the roof and look amazing. Will require bolt anchors or leaving gear.

properties.Name: Geoff's Route 5.7
properties.description: Wet start leads to a wide lay-back flake. Fun-if your into that sort of thing. F.A. Geoff Ris, Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Testarosa 5.4
properties.description: Climb the low angled flake that ends on a ledge. Rap from tree. F.A. Heath Rowland, Keele Shelton

properties.Name: Troll Cave 5.8?
properties.description: No information. F.A. Fletcher Jone

properties.Name: Up Yonder 5.4
properties.description: Super fun and easy dihedral located on a ledge. Looks hard from the ground. Approach via a rhodo filled gully. FA: Heath Rowland Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Dustin's Route 5.9+ pg13
properties.description: F.A. Dustin Stevens

properties.Name: Corn Syrup and Weed 5.7+
properties.description: Short dihedral that ends at a set of chains. FA: Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Sugar Daddy 5.9+
properties.description: It has it all. Good looks, charm... Climb the crack using every technique you know. Finish in the chimney. No big gear needed. F.A. Heath Rowland, Ken Kuper

properties.Name: Polar Opposites 5.11+
properties.description: Climb up to the low roof and dive into jams that decrease in quality near the lip, get strong and pull up onto the face. Climb the jug laden overhanging crack to a fun mantle move. Get it together and climb through the roof and through the short corner. Bolt anchor. FA: Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Blowin Your Lobe 5.11
properties.description: Climb the splitter finger crack til the wall gets steep. Place a pink tricam in a mail slot then launch into the spicy boulder problem. Hang on through two distinct cruxes and a lot of pump. Traverse left to a belay and potential second pitch.

properties.Name: Squirrel Nut Zipper 5.6
properties.description: Geoff Ris pet a squirrel's ass on the FA. Clean easy fun dihedral. If it were only longer... FA: Heath Rowland Geoff Ris Keele Shelton

properties.Name: Bouldering Sucks 5.9
properties.description: Climb the overhanging face to gain the finger crack. Belay at tree. Climb into, then out of the hueco/rockhouse to another tree. The route finishes at the top, but is guarded by a hard off-width. F.A. Heath Rowland Geof Ris

properties.Name: Shake N' Flake 5.7
properties.description: Fun. Strange. Exposed. Grab the giant starting flake just right and you'll find out where the route got it's name. FA Heath Rowland Ashley Kolaya

properties.Name: Pleasant Disapointment 5.9
properties.description: This route looks hard from the ground, but climbs much easier. Steep fingers lead to three fun roofs. FA: Steve Mahon Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Stay Tight 5.10B
properties.description: Five Star classic! Climb 80 feet of awesome crack climbing with a mega splitter finish. FA: Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Lampwrights Street
properties.description: Easy Corner with a tree growing out of it. FA Chris Chaney

properties.Name: Old Men 5.8
properties.description: Fun finger crack and face climbing. FA: Chris Chaney

properties.Name: Hooky M3 WI3
properties.description: First known mixed route in the Red. Follow the smear placing gear in horizontals and the dihedral. Pull a fun move around the bulge at the top. F.A. Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Whisky Bent WI 3
properties.description: If it were only longer.... Climb the thin column to a runnel of sorts. Climb ice and rock to a tree. A potential second pitch could form. FA. Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Mixed Emotions WI4 M4 tr
properties.description: Climb the thin smear to ledge, then take on some steep, juggy mixed terrain above. The thin ice below kept this from being led. It is bitch to setup the TR. F.A. Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Dunkan Gully WI2+
properties.description: Feels like a mini mountain route. Climb a short mixed step to locate a hidden gulley. Climb ice,  frozen turf, and roots up the gully till the angle lets off. Rhodo thrash up hill to a nice fat 30 foot flow. Climb this to the ridge. F.A. Heath Rowland, Tommy Nance

properties.Name: Chocky Bastard 5.7
properties.description: Right angling fat flake with several chockstones to pass. F.A. Heath Rowland, Steve Mahon

properties.Name: Olympia 5.11
properties.description: Climb the chimney to a ledge with a tree. Climb the tree until you can gain the clean overhanging crack. Climb it to an offwidth to the top.

properties.Name: Runnel of Love M4
properties.description: Climb the wide crack with some occasional ice.

properties.Name: Hooks and Crannies M5 WI3
properties.description: With good ice a curtain leads to a series of ledges that end at a chimey. In lean conditions the start will require some heads up conditions. A small roof protects the start of the chimney. Pull the roof then head up the chimney making use of the seam on the left. A crack to the right protects well with hexes(icy). A second pitch could come in with proper conditions. FA: Heath Rowland, Geoff Ris 2016

properties.Name: Boot Brigade Currently 5.6
properties.description: A nice two pitch route. Currently only the first pitch has been done. A nice second pitch is waiting to be done.

properties.Name: We Be Jammin' 5.8
properties.description: Splitter Hand Crack. Jam. SMILE. Repeat. FA Heath Rowland Tommy Nance

properties.Name: Green Machine 5.3
properties.description: FA...who knows. There were no signs of a previous ascent, but this close to Military, who knows.

properties.Name: Feature Creature 5.8
properties.description: Fun splitter-ish crack. Start in a hueco, then boulder out to gain the crack. Climb the wide crack using plates and edges. FA: Heath Rowland Tommy Nance...possibly

properties.Name: Dodging Bullets 5.10R
properties.description: Locate a dual crack system that merges together 40ft from the top. This is the crack on the right that starts off as a chimney, then turns into a hand crack. Climb the steep, sharp hand crack though the large iron roof and belay. Traverse left to the ofwidth and finish on top. Walk climbers left to a tree and rappel. If you fall before the first piece it'll hurt.                          FA Geoff Ris, Heath Rowland

properties.Name: The Crack 5.11+
properties.description: Thin  hands to fingers. Insanely splitter....

properties.Name: Fist Jam or Fail 5.9
properties.description: Lyback and fist jam up huge flake. F.A. Heath Rowland, Jon Jugenheimer, Adam Brusvan

properties.Name: The Red Nose
properties.description: 40 meter adventure climb up the main part of the prow. There is a crack for gear, but most of the climbing is done on the face. FA Jared Leader, Heath Rowland, Mike Wilkinson

properties.Name: Bear Hug 5.9
properties.description: Fat flake on to the left of Fist Jam...F.A. Jared Leader, Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Spider Sanction 5.9
properties.description: Fun chimney that hosts a ton of spiders in the summer. Cool exit from chimney and cool face climbing to ledge. Rap from bolts above Blowin Your Lobe.

properties.Name: Coping Mechanism 5.9R
properties.description: Start the same as Blowin Your Lobe but traverse left and take on the arete. The gear down low isnt great, but the climbing isnt hard.

properties.Name: One Thing Leads To Another 5.8
properties.description: Guide book route...fucking amazing! John Bronaugh Wit Bronaugh

properties.Name: Geoff Jam 5.10x
properties.description: Bring big bros or get rad, way over two tipped out #6's. Bring an orange TCU for the top out 3#6's, a nut to thread through a hole. Or just bring a #Geoff . FA Geoff Ris Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Escape To Reality 5.8
properties.description: Fun wide crack, that doesnt climb like an off-width. standard rack up to #5 FA Heath Rowland Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Paw Paw 5.11
properties.description: 35 meters of fun exposed climbing! FA Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Two Dudes One Truck 5.10- 2p.
properties.description: P1. Climb the crack system to a ledge...fun. P2. Either fire straight up the crack or boulder the overhang to the right(both v1) then work up the funky dihedral. Make a tough move right to a ledge. Shake out and get it back before firing the final, tough offwidth finish. FA Travis Powell Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Thick As Thieves 5.8
properties.description: Climb the fun, varied crack system for about 60feet. Go right at the obvious traverse and tip toe ~30ft  on iron ledges. Great gear.... FA Alton Richardson Geoff Ris Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Lama Drama 5.7
properties.description: Fun hand crack in corner. FA Heath Rowland Will Sweeney

properties.Name: Cant Stop Wont Stop 5.10+
properties.description: Splitter finger and hand crack. Sandy in places...burly... FA Travis Powell Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Open Container 5.7
properties.description: Trad climb...nothing special. FA Jared Leader Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Steppin On Toes 5.10
properties.description: Excellent climb up the face! Super rad slab finish...bring dem TCU's FA Matt Threlfall Jared Leader Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Seneca Seven 5.7
properties.description: Splitter finger crack in the hallway. Its pretty easy if you can finger lock. FA Heath Rowland Jared Leader Matt Threlfall

properties.Name: HBJ 5.9+
properties.description: Climb through a garden and into an amazing dihedral. FA Heath Rowland Travis Powell Will Sweeney

properties.Name: Up To The Nuts 5.10-
properties.description: Climb the beautiful splitter up to a nut anchor...or claw through the muddy offwidth for 20 more feet to the top. May not be manky in the dry season.....FA Heath Rowland Travis Powell Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Inner Vision 5.9 2p
properties.description: Start on boulders and climb to a fun dihedral to ledge. Squirm up a boulder to a large ledge...belay. Pull the roof and chimney to the top. FA-Geoff Ris Amanda Nedved

properties.Name: 80 Ways to Die- 5.8+
properties.description: Climb the fun diheadral(easier than it looks)to a large ledge with tree belay. Un-rope and walk through the massive hallway\chimney. Pick your route and adventure chimney to the summit.        FA-Geoff Ris Bobby Carey Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Birth Canal 5.9
properties.description: This corner is jaw dropping and climbs very well despite have some really wide sections. Tough bushwhack to reach it, but you could be rewarded with a #6 for bootie...if you can bust it free. FA Jared Leader Heath Rolwnad

properties.Name: Wreck It Ralph 5.10+
properties.description: Classic...like really. A perfect 80ft splitter crack that starts fingers and slowly widens to rattly fists. Did I say classic? Tape up.                                FA Heath Rowland Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Black Magic 5.9
properties.description: Climb the right hand crack to the alcove. Pull the roof n face holds and run out the slab to the top. FA Heath Rowland Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Geoff's Route 5.7
properties.description: Take the fun mellow left hand rack.                          FA Geoff Ris Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Follow The Fungus 5.10
properties.description: Beautiful finger crack with a cruxy finish. FA Heath Rowland Geoff Ris

properties.Name: High Five For Booty 5.10
properties.description: Prominent orange right-facing dihedral in an obvious set-back section of the wall. Tech your way up a slabby finger crack boulder problem to a ledge where you can chimney and face climb through easier (and slightly chossier) territory. Extend your gear LONG through the middle to reduce drag around the next corner. Reach awkwardly out left around the roof and into a dihedral with exposed and thrilling plate climbing. Get to the top of the plates and prepare for the final fight through an overhanging offwidth section that may leave you gasping for air on the ledge! Scramble out left to find anchor options, finishing straight up is not worth it.                         FA Geoff Ris, Amanda Nedved

properties.Name: Big Cracks N Slab 5.8
properties.description: Around the next big corner left of High Five, this right-facing dihedral starts with a fist crack (crux) and then gets wider. Bring at least a 5 and 6 each to take for a walk on this one! Varied and very moderate, enjoy this one to the giant detached roof then bail off the gear.                                        FA Geoff Ris

properties.Name: Chimnasium 5.8
properties.description: Chimneys on chimneys on chimneys! A few corners left of Big Cracks, find this one in a large chimney with the wall to your right as you start uphill. Enter the Chimnasium. Wiggle to the top, then pop through a hole to a seclude ledge! Tons of fun!                                                                           FA Geoff Ris Heath Rowland

properties.Name: Canine Crack 5.9
properties.description: Arching finger crack just outside of Chimnasium. Start by climbing the outside of the main chimney, set some gear high, then climb back down and left onto the face. A hand jam bulge takes you to the finger crack and up to a small ledge. Bail here or find a way to the top.                                                  FA Geoff Ris, Ryan Haessely

properties.Name: Mista Crumble Face 5.8X
properties.description: Feels like a horror movie and fun if you like feeling scared and insecure! Pull a bulge to a low ledge and follow a straightforward looking crack up and right. Hint, chip through the bad holds to get the good ones. Easy climbing, but you probably don't want to fall.                     FA Geoff Ris, Kevin Sigmund
